text: Heidegger writes in the Black Notebooks that autumn is not to be seen as a season of death and decay, but the polar opposite, a fiery entrance into "a new time of waking to the unfolding". This is surprisingly close to how Baron Julius Evola describes the logic of initiation.

As in the initiate sees nighttime no longer as an absence of light, but as its non-manifestation. What is lacking physically is instead seen as being at a higher level, in the same way God is not visible. So Heidegger sees autumn as the non-manifestation of spring, life I assume.

They would like cast lots and then go to separate houses w/ each other's spouses or something of the sort. Normies always degenerate to this type of primitive behavior if left on their own. Same as how snakes breed in a giant ball. Every so-called revolution is merely an atavism.
